[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]7. In conclusion, the Government’s claim that no towns and cities will face worse services to London appears t
[normal]o be in conflict with its incorporation of £8.2 billion of classic line savings into the business case for HS2.  Without the
[normal]se
[normal] savings, the HS2 BCR will fall
[normal] significantly
[normal], but with them, it will be 
[normal]extremely 
[normal]difficult, we believe, to maintain 
[normal]the level
[normal]s
[normal] of service 
[normal]to 
[normal]users of 
[normal]current intercity services
[normal] to London
[normal] that the Government claims is their aim
[normal].
